Venizelos Says Greek Bond-Swap Talks Set to Be Held in Athens Next Week

-- B y   M a r c u s   B e n s a s s o n
-- 
2011-12-06T21:49:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/venizelos-says-greek-bond-swap-talks-set-to-be-held-in-athens-next-week.html
Greece  will next week hold talks with
representatives of private sector creditors on the details of a
bond swap aimed at reducing Greece’s debt by 100 billion euros,
Finance Minister Evangelos Venizelos said.  The talks on the debt swap, which was agreed at an Oct. 26
European Union leaders’ summit in Brussels, will begin on Dec.
12 in  Athens , Venizelos told lawmakers in comments televised
live on state-run Vouli TV.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marcus Bensasson in Athens at 
 mbensasson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  